cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses network slicing, software-defined networking, and network function virtualization, which are all related to networking and internet architecture.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a joint resource and admission management algorithm for slice-enabled networks, which involves control and optimization of system resources.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the allocation of resources in a distributed network environment.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to network slicing and resource allocation.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes an algorithm for minimizing the cost of a mobile service provider, which may be related to computational finance.
